6392 
6393 int DocPara::parse()
6394 {
6395  DBG(("DocPara::parse() start\n"));
6396  g_nodeStack.push(this);
6397  // handle style commands "inherited" from the previous paragraph
6398  handleInitialStyleCommands(this,m_children);
6399  int tok;
6400  int retval=0;
6401  while ((tok=doctokenizerYYlex())) // get the next token
6402  {
6403 reparsetoken:
6404  DBG(("token %s at %d",tokToString(tok),doctokenizerYYlineno));
6405  if (tok==TK_WORD || tok==TK_LNKWORD || tok==TK_SYMBOL || tok==TK_URL ||
6406  tok==TK_COMMAND || tok==TK_HTMLTAG
6407  )
6408  {
6409  DBG((" name=%s",qPrint(g_token->name)));
6410  }
6411  DBG(("\n"));
6412  switch(tok)
6413  {
6414  case TK_WORD:
6415  m_children.append(new DocWord(this,g_token->name));
6416  break;
6417  case TK_LNKWORD:
6418  handleLinkedWord(this,m_children);
6419  break;
6420  case TK_URL:
6421  m_children.append(new DocURL(this,g_token->name,g_token->isEMailAddr));
6422  break;
6423  case TK_WHITESPACE:
6424  {
6425  // prevent leading whitespace and collapse multiple whitespace areas
6426  DocNode::Kind k;
6427  if (insidePRE(this) || // all whitespace is relevant
6428  (
6429  // remove leading whitespace
6430  !m_children.isEmpty() &&
6431  // and whitespace after certain constructs
6432  (k=m_children.getLast()->kind())!=DocNode::Kind_HtmlDescList &&
6433  k!=DocNode::Kind_HtmlTable &&
6434  k!=DocNode::Kind_HtmlList &&
6435  k!=DocNode::Kind_SimpleSect &&
6436  k!=DocNode::Kind_AutoList &&
6437  k!=DocNode::Kind_SimpleList &&
6438  /*k!=DocNode::Kind_Verbatim &&*/
6439  k!=DocNode::Kind_HtmlHeader &&
6440  k!=DocNode::Kind_HtmlBlockQuote &&
6441  k!=DocNode::Kind_ParamSect &&
6442  k!=DocNode::Kind_XRefItem
6443  )
6444  )
6445  {
6446  m_children.append(new DocWhiteSpace(this,g_token->chars));
6447  }
6448  }
6449  break;
6450  case TK_LISTITEM:
6451  {
6452  DBG(("found list item at %d parent=%d\n",g_token->indent,parent()->kind()));
6453  DocNode *n=parent();
6454  while (n && n->kind()!=DocNode::Kind_AutoList) n=n->parent();
6455  if (n) // we found an auto list up in the hierarchy
6456  {
6457  DocAutoList *al = (DocAutoList *)n;
6458  DBG(("previous list item at %d\n",al->indent()));
6459  if (al->indent()>=g_token->indent)
6460  // new item at the same or lower indent level
6461  {
6462  retval=TK_LISTITEM;
6463  goto endparagraph;
6464  }
6465  }
6466 
6467  // determine list depth
6468  int depth = 0;
6469  n=parent();
6470  while(n)
6471  {
6472  if (n->kind() == DocNode::Kind_AutoList &&
6473  ((DocAutoList*)n)->isEnumList()) depth++;
6474  n=n->parent();
6475  }
6476 
6477  // first item or sub list => create new list
6478  DocAutoList *al=0;
6479  do
6480  {
6481  al = new DocAutoList(this,g_token->indent,
6482  g_token->isEnumList,depth);
6483  m_children.append(al);
6484  retval = al->parse();
6485  } while (retval==TK_LISTITEM && // new list
6486  al->indent()==g_token->indent // at same indent level
6487  );
6488 
6489  // check the return value
6490  if (retval==RetVal_SimpleSec) // auto list ended due to simple section command
6491  {
6492  // Reparse the token that ended the section at this level,
6493  // so a new simple section will be started at this level.
6494  // This is the same as unputting the last read token and continuing.
6495  g_token->name = g_token->simpleSectName;
6496  if (g_token->name.left(4)=="rcs:") // RCS section
6497  {
6498  g_token->name = g_token->name.mid(4);
6499  g_token->text = g_token->simpleSectText;
6500  tok = TK_RCSTAG;
6501  }
6502  else // other section
6503  {
6504  tok = TK_COMMAND;
6505  }
6506  DBG(("reparsing command %s\n",qPrint(g_token->name)));
6507  goto reparsetoken;
6508  }
6509  else if (retval==TK_ENDLIST)
6510  {
6511  if (al->indent()>g_token->indent) // end list
6512  {
6513  goto endparagraph;
6514  }
6515  else // continue with current paragraph
6516  {
6517  }
6518  }
6519  else // paragraph ended due to TK_NEWPARA, TK_LISTITEM, or EOF
6520  {
6521  goto endparagraph;
6522  }
6523  }
6524  break;
6525  case TK_ENDLIST:
6526  DBG(("Found end of list inside of paragraph at line %d\n",doctokenizerYYlineno));
6527  if (parent()->kind()==DocNode::Kind_AutoListItem)
6528  {
6529  ASSERT(parent()->parent()->kind()==DocNode::Kind_AutoList);
6530  DocAutoList *al = (DocAutoList *)parent()->parent();
6531  if (al->indent()>=g_token->indent)
6532  {
6533  // end of list marker ends this paragraph
6534  retval=TK_ENDLIST;
6535  goto endparagraph;
6536  }
6537  else
6538  {
6539  warn_doc_error(g_fileName,doctokenizerYYlineno,"End of list marker found "
6540  "has invalid indent level");
6541  }
6542  }
6543  else
6544  {
6545  warn_doc_error(g_fileName,doctokenizerYYlineno,"End of list marker found without any preceding "
6546  "list items");
6547  }
6548  break;
6549  case TK_COMMAND:
6550  {
6551  // see if we have to start a simple section
6552  int cmd = Mappers::cmdMapper->map(g_token->name);
6553  DocNode *n=parent();
6554  while (n &&
6555  n->kind()!=DocNode::Kind_SimpleSect &&
6556  n->kind()!=DocNode::Kind_ParamSect
6557  )
6558  {
6559  n=n->parent();
6560  }
6561  if (cmd&SIMPLESECT_BIT)
6562  {
6563  if (n) // already in a simple section
6564  {
6565  // simple section cannot start in this paragraph, need
6566  // to unwind the stack and remember the command.
6567  g_token->simpleSectName = g_token->name.copy();
6568  retval=RetVal_SimpleSec;
6569  goto endparagraph;
6570  }
6571  }
6572  // see if we are in a simple list
6573  n=parent();
6574  while (n && n->kind()!=DocNode::Kind_SimpleListItem) n=n->parent();
6575  if (n)
6576  {
6577  if (cmd==CMD_LI)
6578  {
6579  retval=RetVal_ListItem;
6580  goto endparagraph;
6581  }
6582  }
6583 
6584  // handle the command
6585  retval=handleCommand(g_token->name);
6586  DBG(("handleCommand returns %x\n",retval));
6587 
6588  // check the return value
6589  if (retval==RetVal_SimpleSec)
6590  {
6591  // Reparse the token that ended the section at this level,
6592  // so a new simple section will be started at this level.
6593  // This is the same as unputting the last read token and continuing.
6594  g_token->name = g_token->simpleSectName;
6595  if (g_token->name.left(4)=="rcs:") // RCS section
6596  {
6597  g_token->name = g_token->name.mid(4);
6598  g_token->text = g_token->simpleSectText;
6599  tok = TK_RCSTAG;
6600  }
6601  else // other section
6602  {
6603  tok = TK_COMMAND;
6604  }
6605  DBG(("reparsing command %s\n",qPrint(g_token->name)));
6606  goto reparsetoken;
6607  }
6608  else if (retval==RetVal_OK)
6609  {
6610  // the command ended normally, keep scanning for new tokens.
6611  retval = 0;
6612  }
6613  else if (retval>0 && retval<RetVal_OK)
6614  {
6615  // the command ended with a new command, reparse this token
6616  tok = retval;
6617  goto reparsetoken;
6618  }
6619  else // end of file, end of paragraph, start or end of section
6620  // or some auto list marker
6621  {
6622  goto endparagraph;
6623  }
6624  }
6625  break;
6626  case TK_HTMLTAG:
6627  {
6628  if (!g_token->endTag) // found a start tag
6629  {
6630  retval = handleHtmlStartTag(g_token->name,g_token->attribs);
6631  }
6632  else // found an end tag
6633  {
6634  retval = handleHtmlEndTag(g_token->name);
6635  }
6636  if (retval==RetVal_OK)
6637  {
6638  // the command ended normally, keep scanner for new tokens.
6639  retval = 0;
6640  }
6641  else
6642  {
6643  goto endparagraph;
6644  }
6645  }
6646  break;
6647  case TK_SYMBOL:
6648  {
6649  DocSymbol::SymType s = DocSymbol::decodeSymbol(g_token->name);
6650  if (s!=DocSymbol::Sym_Unknown)
6651  {
6652  m_children.append(new DocSymbol(this,s));
6653  }
6654  else
6655  {
6656  warn_doc_error(g_fileName,doctokenizerYYlineno,"Unsupported symbol %s found",
6657  qPrint(g_token->name));
6658  }
6659  break;
6660  }
6661  case TK_NEWPARA:
6662  retval=TK_NEWPARA;
6663  goto endparagraph;
6664  case TK_RCSTAG:
6665  {
6666  DocNode *n=parent();
6667  while (n &&
6668  n->kind()!=DocNode::Kind_SimpleSect &&
6669  n->kind()!=DocNode::Kind_ParamSect
6670  )
6671  {
6672  n=n->parent();
6673  }
6674  if (n) // already in a simple section
6675  {
6676  // simple section cannot start in this paragraph, need
6677  // to unwind the stack and remember the command.
6678  g_token->simpleSectName = "rcs:"+g_token->name;
6679  g_token->simpleSectText = g_token->text;
6680  retval=RetVal_SimpleSec;
6681  goto endparagraph;
6682  }
6683 
6684  // see if we are in a simple list
6685  DocSimpleSect *ss=new DocSimpleSect(this,DocSimpleSect::Rcs);
6686  m_children.append(ss);
6687  ss->parseRcs();
6688  }
6689  break;
6690  default:
6691  warn_doc_error(g_fileName,doctokenizerYYlineno,
6692  "Found unexpected token (id=%x)\n",tok);
6693  break;
6694  }
6695  }
6696  retval=0;
6697 endparagraph:
6698  handlePendingStyleCommands(this,m_children);
6699  DocNode *n = g_nodeStack.pop();
6700  ASSERT(n==this);
6701  DBG(("DocPara::parse() end retval=%x\n",retval));
6702  INTERNAL_ASSERT(retval==0 || retval==TK_NEWPARA || retval==TK_LISTITEM ||
6703  retval==TK_ENDLIST || retval>RetVal_OK
6704  );
6705 
6706  return retval;
6707 }
6708 
6709 //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
6710 
6711 int DocSection::parse()
6712 {
6713  DBG(("DocSection::parse() start %s level=%d\n",qPrint(g_token->sectionId),m_level));
6714  int retval=RetVal_OK;
6715  g_nodeStack.push(this);
6716 
6717  SectionInfo *sec;
6718  if (!m_id.isEmpty())
6719  {
6720  sec=Doxygen::sectionDict->find(m_id);
6721  if (sec)
6722  {
6723  m_file = sec->fileName;
6724  m_anchor = sec->label;
6725  m_title = sec->title;
6726  if (m_title.isEmpty()) m_title = sec->label;
6727  if (g_sectionDict && g_sectionDict->find(m_id)==0)
6728  {
6729  g_sectionDict->append(m_id,sec);
6730  }
6731  }
6732  }
6733 
6734  // first parse any number of paragraphs
6735  bool isFirst=TRUE;
6736  DocPara *lastPar=0;
6737  do
6738  {
6739  DocPara *par = new DocPara(this);
6740  if (isFirst) { par->markFirst(); isFirst=FALSE; }
6741  retval=par->parse();
6742  if (!par->isEmpty())
6743  {
6744  m_children.append(par);
6745  lastPar=par;
6746  }
6747  else
6748  {
6749  delete par;
6750  }
6751  if (retval==TK_LISTITEM)
6752  {
6753  warn_doc_error(g_fileName,doctokenizerYYlineno,"Invalid list item found");
6754  }
6755  if (retval==RetVal_Internal)
6756  {
6757  DocInternal *in = new DocInternal(this);
6758  m_children.append(in);
6759  retval = in->parse(m_level+1);
6760  if (retval==RetVal_EndInternal)
6761  {
6762  retval=RetVal_OK;
6763  }
6764  }
6765  } while (retval!=0 &&
6766  retval!=RetVal_Section &&
6767  retval!=RetVal_Subsection &&
6768  retval!=RetVal_Subsubsection &&
6769  retval!=RetVal_Paragraph &&
6770  retval!=RetVal_EndInternal
6771  );
6772 
6773  if (lastPar) lastPar->markLast();
6774 
6775  //printf("m_level=%d <-> %d\n",m_level,Doxygen::subpageNestingLevel);
6776 
6777  if (retval==RetVal_Subsection && m_level==Doxygen::subpageNestingLevel+1)
6778  {
6779  // then parse any number of nested sections
6780  while (retval==RetVal_Subsection) // more sections follow
6781  {
6782  //SectionInfo *sec=Doxygen::sectionDict[g_token->sectionId];
6783  DocSection *s=new DocSection(this,
6784  QMIN(2+Doxygen::subpageNestingLevel,5),g_token->sectionId);
6785  m_children.append(s);
6786  retval = s->parse();
6787  }
6788  }
6789  else if (retval==RetVal_Subsubsection && m_level==Doxygen::subpageNestingLevel+2)
6790  {
6791  // then parse any number of nested sections
6792  while (retval==RetVal_Subsubsection) // more sections follow
6793  {
6794  //SectionInfo *sec=Doxygen::sectionDict[g_token->sectionId];
6795  DocSection *s=new DocSection(this,
6796  QMIN(3+Doxygen::subpageNestingLevel,5),g_token->sectionId);
6797  m_children.append(s);
6798  retval = s->parse();
6799  }
6800  }
6801  else if (retval==RetVal_Paragraph && m_level==QMIN(5,Doxygen::subpageNestingLevel+3))
6802  {
6803  // then parse any number of nested sections
6804  while (retval==RetVal_Paragraph) // more sections follow
6805  {
6806  //SectionInfo *sec=Doxygen::sectionDict[g_token->sectionId];
6807  DocSection *s=new DocSection(this,
6808  QMIN(4+Doxygen::subpageNestingLevel,5),g_token->sectionId);
6809  m_children.append(s);
6810  retval = s->parse();
6811  }
6812  }
6813  else if ((m_level<=1+Doxygen::subpageNestingLevel && retval==RetVal_Subsubsection) ||
6814  (m_level<=2+Doxygen::subpageNestingLevel && retval==RetVal_Paragraph)
6815  )
6816  {
6817  int level = (retval==RetVal_Subsubsection) ? 3 : 4;
6818  warn_doc_error(g_fileName,doctokenizerYYlineno,"Unexpected %s "
6819  "command found inside %s!",
6820  sectionLevelToName[level],sectionLevelToName[m_level]);
6821  retval=0; // stop parsing
6822  }
6823  else
6824  {
6825  }
6826 
6827  INTERNAL_ASSERT(retval==0 ||
6828  retval==RetVal_Section ||
6829  retval==RetVal_Subsection ||
6830  retval==RetVal_Subsubsection ||
6831  retval==RetVal_Paragraph ||
6832  retval==RetVal_Internal ||
6833  retval==RetVal_EndInternal
6834  );
6835 
6836  DBG(("DocSection::parse() end: retval=%x\n",retval));
6837  DocNode *n = g_nodeStack.pop();
6838  ASSERT(n==this);
6839  return retval;
6840 }
6841 
6842 //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
6843 
6844 void DocText::parse()
6845 {
6846  DBG(("DocText::parse() start\n"));
6847  g_nodeStack.push(this);
6848  doctokenizerYYsetStateText();
6849 
6850  int tok;
6851  while ((tok=doctokenizerYYlex())) // get the next token
6852  {
6853  switch(tok)
6854  {
6855  case TK_WORD:
6856  m_children.append(new DocWord(this,g_token->name));
6857  break;
6858  case TK_WHITESPACE:
6859  m_children.append(new DocWhiteSpace(this,g_token->chars));
6860  break;
6861  case TK_SYMBOL:
6862  {
6863  DocSymbol::SymType s = DocSymbol::decodeSymbol(g_token->name);
6864  if (s!=DocSymbol::Sym_Unknown)
6865  {
6866  m_children.append(new DocSymbol(this,s));
6867  }
6868  else
6869  {
6870  warn_doc_error(g_fileName,doctokenizerYYlineno,"Unsupported symbol %s found",
6871  qPrint(g_token->name));
6872  }
6873  }
6874  break;
6875  case TK_COMMAND:
6876  switch (Mappers::cmdMapper->map(g_token->name))
6877  {
6878  case CMD_BSLASH:
6879  m_children.append(new DocSymbol(this,DocSymbol::Sym_BSlash));
6880  break;
6881  case CMD_AT:
6882  m_children.append(new DocSymbol(this,DocSymbol::Sym_At));
6883  break;
6884  case CMD_LESS:
6885  m_children.append(new DocSymbol(this,DocSymbol::Sym_Less));
6886  break;
6887  case CMD_GREATER:
6888  m_children.append(new DocSymbol(this,DocSymbol::Sym_Greater));
6889  break;
6890  case CMD_AMP:
6891  m_children.append(new DocSymbol(this,DocSymbol::Sym_Amp));
6892  break;
6893  case CMD_DOLLAR:
6894  m_children.append(new DocSymbol(this,DocSymbol::Sym_Dollar));
6895  break;
6896  case CMD_HASH:
6897  m_children.append(new DocSymbol(this,DocSymbol::Sym_Hash));
6898  break;
6899  case CMD_DCOLON:
6900  m_children.append(new DocSymbol(this,DocSymbol::Sym_DoubleColon));
6901  break;
6902  case CMD_PERCENT:
6903  m_children.append(new DocSymbol(this,DocSymbol::Sym_Percent));
6904  break;
6905  case CMD_NDASH:
6906  m_children.append(new DocSymbol(this,DocSymbol::Sym_Minus));
6907  m_children.append(new DocSymbol(this,DocSymbol::Sym_Minus));
6908  break;
6909  case CMD_MDASH:
6910  m_children.append(new DocSymbol(this,DocSymbol::Sym_Minus));
6911  m_children.append(new DocSymbol(this,DocSymbol::Sym_Minus));
6912  m_children.append(new DocSymbol(this,DocSymbol::Sym_Minus));
6913  break;
6914  case CMD_QUOTE:
6915  m_children.append(new DocSymbol(this,DocSymbol::Sym_Quot));
6916  break;
6917  case CMD_PUNT:
6918  m_children.append(new DocSymbol(this,DocSymbol::Sym_Dot));
6919  break;
6920  case CMD_PLUS:
6921  m_children.append(new DocSymbol(this,DocSymbol::Sym_Plus));
6922  break;
6923  case CMD_MINUS:
6924  m_children.append(new DocSymbol(this,DocSymbol::Sym_Minus));
6925  break;
6926  default:
6927  warn_doc_error(g_fileName,doctokenizerYYlineno,"Unexpected command `%s' found",
6928  qPrint(g_token->name));
6929  break;
6930  }
6931  break;
6932  default:
6933  warn_doc_error(g_fileName,doctokenizerYYlineno,"Unexpected token %s",
6934  tokToString(tok));
6935  break;
6936  }
6937  }
6938 
6939  handleUnclosedStyleCommands();
6940 
6941  DocNode *n = g_nodeStack.pop();
6942  ASSERT(n==this);
6943  DBG(("DocText::parse() end\n"));
6944 }
6945 
6946 
6947 //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
6948 
6949 void DocRoot::parse()
6950 {
6951  DBG(("DocRoot::parse() start\n"));
6952  g_nodeStack.push(this);
6953  doctokenizerYYsetStatePara();
6954  int retval=0;
6955 
6956  // first parse any number of paragraphs
6957  bool isFirst=TRUE;
6958  DocPara *lastPar=0;
6959  do
6960  {
6961  DocPara *par = new DocPara(this);
6962  if (isFirst) { par->markFirst(); isFirst=FALSE; }
6963  retval=par->parse();
6964  if (!par->isEmpty())
6965  {
6966  m_children.append(par);
6967  lastPar=par;
6968  }
6969  else
6970  {
6971  delete par;
6972  }
6973  if (retval==TK_LISTITEM)
6974  {
6975  warn_doc_error(g_fileName,doctokenizerYYlineno,"Invalid list item found");
6976  }
6977  else if (retval==RetVal_Subsection)
6978  {
6979  warn_doc_error(g_fileName,doctokenizerYYlineno,"found subsection command outside of section context!");
6980  }
6981  else if (retval==RetVal_Subsubsection)
6982  {
6983  warn_doc_error(g_fileName,doctokenizerYYlineno,"found subsubsection command outside of subsection context!");
6984  }
6985  else if (retval==RetVal_Paragraph)
6986  {
6987  warn_doc_error(g_fileName,doctokenizerYYlineno,"found paragraph command outside of subsubsection context!");
6988  }
6989  if (retval==RetVal_Internal)
6990  {
6991  DocInternal *in = new DocInternal(this);
6992  m_children.append(in);
6993  retval = in->parse(1);
6994  }
6995  } while (retval!=0 && retval!=RetVal_Section);
6996  if (lastPar) lastPar->markLast();
6997 
6998  //printf("DocRoot::parse() retval=%d %d\n",retval,RetVal_Section);
6999  // then parse any number of level1 sections
7000  while (retval==RetVal_Section)
7001  {
7002  SectionInfo *sec=Doxygen::sectionDict->find(g_token->sectionId);
7003  if (sec)
7004  {
7005  DocSection *s=new DocSection(this,
7006  QMIN(1+Doxygen::subpageNestingLevel,5),g_token->sectionId);
7007  m_children.append(s);
7008  retval = s->parse();
7009  }
7010  else
7011  {
7012  warn_doc_error(g_fileName,doctokenizerYYlineno,"Invalid section id `%s'; ignoring section",qPrint(g_token->sectionId));
7013  retval = 0;
7014  }
7015  }
7016 
7017  handleUnclosedStyleCommands();
7018 
7019  DocNode *n = g_nodeStack.pop();
7020  ASSERT(n==this);
7021  DBG(("DocRoot::parse() end\n"));
7022 }
7023 
7024 static QCString extractCopyDocId(const char *data, uint &j, uint len)
7025 {
7026  uint s=j;
7027  uint e=j;
7028  int round=0;
7029  bool insideDQuote=FALSE;
7030  bool insideSQuote=FALSE;
7031  bool found=FALSE;
7032  while (j<len && !found)
7033  {
7034  if (!insideSQuote && !insideDQuote)
7035  {
7036  switch (data[j])
7037  {
7038  case '(': round++; break;
7039  case ')': round--; break;
7040  case '"': insideDQuote=TRUE; break;
7041  case '\'': insideSQuote=TRUE; break;
7042  case ' ': // fall through
7043  case '\t': // fall through
7044  case '\n':
7045  found=(round==0);
7046  break;
7047  }
7048  }
7049  else if (insideSQuote) // look for single quote end
7050  {
7051  if (data[j]=='\'' && (j==0 || data[j]!='\\'))
7052  {
7053  insideSQuote=FALSE;
7054  }
7055  }
7056  else if (insideDQuote) // look for double quote end
7057  {
7058  if (data[j]=='"' && (j==0 || data[j]!='\\'))
7059  {
7060  insideDQuote=FALSE;
7061  }
7062  }
7063  if (!found) j++;
7064  }
7065  if (qstrncmp(data+j," const",6)==0)
7066  {
7067  j+=6;
7068  }
7069  else if (qstrncmp(data+j," volatile",9)==0)
7070  {
7071  j+=9;
7072  }
7073  e=j;
7074  QCString id(e-s+1);
7075  if (e>s) memcpy(id.rawData(),data+s,e-s);
7076  id.at(e-s)='\0';
7077  //printf("extractCopyDocId='%s' input='%s'\n",id.data(),&data[s]);
7078  return id;
7079 }
7080 
7081 // macro to check if the input starts with a specific command.
7082 // note that data[i] should point to the start of the command (\ or @ character)
7083 // and the sizeof(str) returns the size of str including the '\0' terminator;
7084 // a fact we abuse to skip over the start of the command character.
7085 #define CHECK_FOR_COMMAND(str,action) \
7086  do if ((i+sizeof(str)<len) && qstrncmp(data+i+1,str,sizeof(str)-1)==0) \
7087  { j=i+sizeof(str); action; } while(0)
7088 
7089 static uint isCopyBriefOrDetailsCmd(const char *data, uint i,uint len,bool &brief)
7090 {
7091  int j=0;
7092  if (i==0 || (data[i-1]!='@' && data[i-1]!='\\')) // not an escaped command
7093  {
7094  CHECK_FOR_COMMAND("copybrief",brief=TRUE); // @copybrief or \copybrief
7095  CHECK_FOR_COMMAND("copydetails",brief=FALSE); // @copydetails or \copydetails
7096  }
7097  return j;
7098 }
7099 
7100 static uint isVerbatimSection(const char *data,uint i,uint len,QCString &endMarker)
7101 {
7102  int j=0;
7103  if (i==0 || (data[i-1]!='@' && data[i-1]!='\\')) // not an escaped command
7104  {
7105  CHECK_FOR_COMMAND("dot",endMarker="enddot");
7106  CHECK_FOR_COMMAND("code",endMarker="endcode");
7107  CHECK_FOR_COMMAND("msc",endMarker="endmsc");
7108  CHECK_FOR_COMMAND("verbatim",endMarker="endverbatim");
7109  CHECK_FOR_COMMAND("latexonly",endMarker="endlatexonly");
7110  CHECK_FOR_COMMAND("htmlonly",endMarker="endhtmlonly");
7111  CHECK_FOR_COMMAND("xmlonly",endMarker="endxmlonly");
7112  CHECK_FOR_COMMAND("rtfonly",endMarker="endrtfonly");
7113  CHECK_FOR_COMMAND("manonly",endMarker="endmanonly");
7114  CHECK_FOR_COMMAND("docbookonly",endMarker="enddocbookonly");
7115  CHECK_FOR_COMMAND("startuml",endMarker="enduml");
7116  }
7117  //printf("isVerbatimSection(%s)=%d)\n",QCString(&data[i]).left(10).data(),j);
7118  return j;
7119 }
7120 
7121 static uint skipToEndMarker(const char *data,uint i,uint len,const QCString &endMarker)
7122 {
7123  while (i<len)
7124  {
7125  if ((data[i]=='@' || data[i]=='\\') && // start of command character
7126  (i==0 || (data[i-1]!='@' && data[i-1]!='\\'))) // that is not escaped
7127  {
7128  if (i+endMarker.length()+1<=len && qstrncmp(data+i+1,endMarker,endMarker.length())==0)
7129  {
7130  return i+endMarker.length()+1;
7131  }
7132  }
7133  i++;
7134  }
7135  // oops no endmarker found...
7136  return i<len ? i+1 : len;
7137 }
7138 
7139 static QCString processCopyDoc(const char *data,uint &len)
7140 {
7141  //printf("processCopyDoc start '%s'\n",data);
7142  GrowBuf buf;
7143  uint i=0;
7144  while (i<len)
7145  {
7146  char c = data[i];
7147  if (c=='@' || c=='\\') // look for a command
7148  {
7149  bool isBrief=TRUE;
7150  uint j=isCopyBriefOrDetailsCmd(data,i,len,isBrief);
7151  if (j>0)
7152  {
7153  // skip whitespace
7154  while (j<len && (data[j]==' ' || data[j]=='\t')) j++;
7155  // extract the argument
7156  QCString id = extractCopyDocId(data,j,len);
7157  Definition *def;
7158  QCString doc,brief;
7159  //printf("resolving docs='%s'\n",id.data());
7160  if (findDocsForMemberOrCompound(id,&doc,&brief,&def))
7161  {
7162  //printf("found it def=%p brief='%s' doc='%s' isBrief=%d\n",def,brief.data(),doc.data(),isBrief);
7163  if (g_copyStack.findRef(def)==-1) // definition not parsed earlier
7164  {
7165  g_copyStack.append(def);
7166  if (isBrief)
7167  {
7168  uint l=brief.length();
7169  buf.addStr(processCopyDoc(brief,l));
7170  }
7171  else
7172  {
7173  uint l=doc.length();
7174  buf.addStr(processCopyDoc(doc,l));
7175  }
7176  g_copyStack.remove(def);
7177  }
7178  else
7179  {
7180  warn_doc_error(g_fileName,doctokenizerYYlineno,
7181  "Found recursive @copy%s or @copydoc relation for argument '%s'.\n",
7182  isBrief?"brief":"details",id.data());
7183  }
7184  }
7185  else
7186  {
7187  warn_doc_error(g_fileName,doctokenizerYYlineno,
7188  "@copy%s or @copydoc target '%s' not found", isBrief?"brief":"details",
7189  id.data());
7190  }
7191  // skip over command
7192  i=j;
7193  }
7194  else
7195  {
7196  QCString endMarker;
7197  uint k = isVerbatimSection(data,i,len,endMarker);
7198  if (k>0)
7199  {
7200  int orgPos = i;
7201  i=skipToEndMarker(data,k,len,endMarker);
7202  buf.addStr(data+orgPos,i-orgPos);
7203  }
7204  else
7205  {
7206  buf.addChar(c);
7207  i++;
7208  }
7209  }
7210  }
7211  else // not a command, just copy
7212  {
7213  buf.addChar(c);
7214  i++;
7215  }
7216  }
7217  len = buf.getPos();
7218  buf.addChar(0);
7219  return buf.get();
7220 }
7221

7224 DocRoot *validatingParseDoc(const char *fileName,int startLine,
7225  Definition *ctx,MemberDef *md,
7226  const char *input,bool indexWords,
7227  bool isExample, const char *exampleName,
7228  bool singleLine, bool linkFromIndex)
7229 {
7230  //printf("validatingParseDoc(%s,%s)=[%s]\n",ctx?ctx->name().data():"<none>",
7231  // md?md->name().data():"<none>",
7232  // input);
7233  //printf("========== validating %s at line %d\n",fileName,startLine);
7234  //printf("---------------- input --------------------\n%s\n----------- end input -------------------\n",input);
7235  //g_token = new TokenInfo;
7236 
7237  // store parser state so we can re-enter this function if needed
7238  //bool fortranOpt = Config_getBool(OPTIMIZE_FOR_FORTRAN);
7239  docParserPushContext();
7240 
7241  if (ctx && ctx!=Doxygen::globalScope &&
7242  (ctx->definitionType()==Definition::TypeClass ||
7243  ctx->definitionType()==Definition::TypeNamespace
7244  )
7245  )
7246  {
7247  g_context = ctx->name();
7248  }
7249  else if (ctx && ctx->definitionType()==Definition::TypePage)
7250  {
7251  Definition *scope = ((PageDef*)ctx)->getPageScope();
7252  if (scope && scope!=Doxygen::globalScope) g_context = scope->name();
7253  }
7254  else if (ctx && ctx->definitionType()==Definition::TypeGroup)
7255  {
7256  Definition *scope = ((GroupDef*)ctx)->getGroupScope();
7257  if (scope && scope!=Doxygen::globalScope) g_context = scope->name();
7258  }
7259  else
7260  {
7261  g_context = "";
7262  }
7263  g_scope = ctx;
7264 
7265  if (indexWords && Doxygen::searchIndex)
7266  {
7267  if (md)
7268  {
7269  g_searchUrl=md->getOutputFileBase();
7270  Doxygen::searchIndex->setCurrentDoc(md,md->anchor(),FALSE);
7271  }
7272  else if (ctx)
7273  {
7274  g_searchUrl=ctx->getOutputFileBase();
7275  Doxygen::searchIndex->setCurrentDoc(ctx,ctx->anchor(),FALSE);
7276  }
7277  }
7278 #if 0
7279  if (indexWords && md && Doxygen::searchIndex)
7280  {
7281  g_searchUrl=md->getOutputFileBase();
7282  Doxygen::searchIndex->setCurrentDoc(
7283  (md->getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_Fortran ?
7284  theTranslator->trSubprogram(TRUE,TRUE):
7285  theTranslator->trMember(TRUE,TRUE))+" "+md->qualifiedName(),
7286  g_searchUrl,
7287  md->anchor());
7288  }
7289  else if (indexWords && ctx && Doxygen::searchIndex)
7290  {
7291  g_searchUrl=ctx->getOutputFileBase();
7292  QCString name = ctx->qualifiedName();
7293 
7294  SrcLangExt lang = ctx->getLanguage();
7295  QCString sep = getLanguageSpecificSeparator(lang);
7296  if (sep!="::")
7297  {
7298  name = substitute(name,"::",sep);
7299  }
7300 
7301  switch (ctx->definitionType())
7302  {
7303  case Definition::TypePage:
7304  {
7305  PageDef *pd = (PageDef *)ctx;
7306  if (!pd->title().isEmpty())
7307  {
7308  name = theTranslator->trPage(TRUE,TRUE)+" "+pd->title();
7309  }
7310  else
7311  {
7312  name = theTranslator->trPage(TRUE,TRUE)+" "+pd->name();
7313  }
7314  }
7315  break;
7316  case Definition::TypeClass:
7317  {
7318  ClassDef *cd = (ClassDef *)ctx;
7319  name.prepend(cd->compoundTypeString()+" ");
7320  }
7321  break;
7322  case Definition::TypeNamespace:
7323  {
7324  if (lang==SrcLangExt_Java || lang==SrcLangExt_CSharp)
7325  {
7326  name = theTranslator->trPackage(name);
7327  }
7328  else if (lang==SrcLangExt_Fortran)
7329  {
7330  name.prepend(theTranslator->trModule(TRUE,TRUE)+" ");
7331  }
7332  else
7333  {
7334  name.prepend(theTranslator->trNamespace(TRUE,TRUE)+" ");
7335  }
7336  }
7337  break;
7338  case Definition::TypeGroup:
7339  {
7340  GroupDef *gd = (GroupDef *)ctx;
7341  if (gd->groupTitle())
7342  {
7343  name = theTranslator->trGroup(TRUE,TRUE)+" "+gd->groupTitle();
7344  }
7345  else
7346  {
7347  name.prepend(theTranslator->trGroup(TRUE,TRUE)+" ");
7348  }
7349  }
7350  break;
7351  default:
7352  break;
7353  }
7354  Doxygen::searchIndex->setCurrentDoc(name,g_searchUrl);
7355  }
7356 #endif
7357  else
7358  {
7359  g_searchUrl="";
7360  }
7361 
7362  g_fileName = fileName;
7363  g_relPath = (!linkFromIndex && ctx) ?
7364  QCString(relativePathToRoot(ctx->getOutputFileBase())) :
7365  QCString("");
7366  //printf("ctx->name=%s relPath=%s\n",ctx->name().data(),g_relPath.data());
7367  g_memberDef = md;
7368  g_nodeStack.clear();
7369  g_styleStack.clear();
7370  g_initialStyleStack.clear();
7371  g_inSeeBlock = FALSE;
7372  g_xmlComment = FALSE;
7373  g_insideHtmlLink = FALSE;
7374  g_includeFileText = "";
7375  g_includeFileOffset = 0;
7376  g_includeFileLength = 0;
7377  g_isExample = isExample;
7378  g_exampleName = exampleName;
7379  g_hasParamCommand = FALSE;
7380  g_hasReturnCommand = FALSE;
7381  g_paramsFound.setAutoDelete(FALSE);
7382  g_paramsFound.clear();
7383  g_sectionDict = 0; //sections;
7384 
7385  //printf("Starting comment block at %s:%d\n",g_fileName.data(),startLine);
7386  doctokenizerYYlineno=startLine;
7387  uint inpLen=qstrlen(input);
7388  QCString inpStr = processCopyDoc(input,inpLen);
7389  if (inpStr.isEmpty() || inpStr.at(inpStr.length()-1)!='\n')
7390  {
7391  inpStr+='\n';
7392  }
7393  //printf("processCopyDoc(in='%s' out='%s')\n",input,inpStr.data());
7394  doctokenizerYYinit(inpStr,g_fileName);
7395 
7396  // build abstract syntax tree
7397  DocRoot *root = new DocRoot(md!=0,singleLine);
7398  root->parse();
7399 
7400 
7401  if (Debug::isFlagSet(Debug::PrintTree))
7402  {
7403  // pretty print the result
7404  PrintDocVisitor *v = new PrintDocVisitor;
7405  root->accept(v);
7406  delete v;
7407  }
7408 
7409  checkUndocumentedParams();
7410  detectNoDocumentedParams();
7411 
7412  // TODO: These should be called at the end of the program.
7413  //doctokenizerYYcleanup();
7414  //Mappers::cmdMapper->freeInstance();
7415  //Mappers::htmlTagMapper->freeInstance();
7416 
7417  // restore original parser state
7418  docParserPopContext();
7419 
7420  //printf(">>>>>> end validatingParseDoc(%s,%s)\n",ctx?ctx->name().data():"<none>",
7421  // md?md->name().data():"<none>");
7422 
7423  return root;
7424 }

7456

7458  {
7459  doctokenizerYYlineno=1;
7460  doctokenizerYYinit(input,g_fileName);
7461

7463  txt->parse();
7464

7471  }
7472  }
7473 
7474  // restore original parser state
7475  docParserPopContext();
7476  return txt;
